#Images
---

Images should be supplied in .jpg format at the largest size available.

For optimum quality vs file size, the images should be 2x actual display size and saved at 40%
quality. Whilst image may appear slightly pixelated at actual size, when render in the email at half-size,
it should look sharp.

> **IMPORTANT** The aspect ratio of final images MUST match the template spec, otherwise they are liable to break the
    layout in Outlook.

